WEBVTT

00:00.006 --> 00:01.472
[ARCHIE] <i> Previously on</i> Riverdale...

00:01.541 --> 00:03.374
Thank you for agreeing
to help me.

00:03.443 --> 00:05.376
If I could go undercover,
I would.

00:05.445 --> 00:08.212
Have you ever experienced
the loss of a loved one?

00:08.281 --> 00:09.247
My brother Jason.

00:09.316 --> 00:11.015
[EDGAR] Memories are often painful.

00:11.084 --> 00:12.550
But they don't have to be.

00:12.619 --> 00:14.385
[CHERYL] <i> Well,
I'm done being your mole.</i>

00:14.454 --> 00:16.588
Okay. Well, you should stop going to
the Farm before Edgar catches on to you.

00:16.656 --> 00:17.889
I'm still going to go.

00:17.958 --> 00:20.725
Is the reason you're
so obsessed with the Farm

00:20.794 --> 00:23.127
because they let you
talk to Charles?

00:23.196 --> 00:24.596
Yes. I see my son.

00:24.664 --> 00:27.031
[EDGAR] Tell me.
What do you want to know?

00:27.100 --> 00:27.932
Everything.

00:28.001 --> 00:29.434
Start from the beginning.

00:29.502 --> 00:31.302
Ricky, listen to me,
you don't want to do this.

00:31.371 --> 00:34.372
If I don't do this, the
Gargoyles, they won't protect me.

00:34.441 --> 00:35.974
[ARCHIE] <i> Jug, Mad Dog was right.</i>

00:36.042 --> 00:37.942
<i>I saw Gargoyles coming in and
out like they own the place.</i>

00:38.011 --> 00:39.978
[JUGHEAD] <i> That must be where
Kurtz is doing his cooking.</i>

00:40.046 --> 00:41.312
I'm ready to ascend.

00:41.381 --> 00:42.380
- Are you?
- [JUGHEAD YELLS]

00:46.085 --> 00:47.918
Elio hooked me up with
a house on the Northside.

00:47.987 --> 00:49.586
So, what?
You have to fight for him?

00:49.655 --> 00:51.288
Come on, man.
You saw that place.

00:51.357 --> 00:53.523
[FP] Terry, I'm getting
close to the clearing.

00:53.592 --> 00:54.825
I don't see any...

01:02.468 --> 01:04.034
Poor Baby Teeth.

01:04.102 --> 01:07.404
Brandon Morris was his real name.
We ID'ed him from his prints.

01:07.473 --> 01:08.639
First glance,

01:08.707 --> 01:10.774
very similar to how you found
Ben and Dilton.

01:10.843 --> 01:13.010
But I don't know.

01:14.380 --> 01:16.613
I need your help, son, please.

01:18.651 --> 01:19.650
Yeah, of course.

01:23.122 --> 01:25.589
These blue lips are the same.

01:25.658 --> 01:27.658
Markings on his back
are the same, too.

01:28.360 --> 01:29.359
[CAMERA CLICKS]

01:32.097 --> 01:34.831
But his missing teeth,
that's the twist.

01:38.404 --> 01:40.070
[JUGHEAD SIGHS]

01:40.139 --> 01:41.672
This might be a copycat killer.

01:41.740 --> 01:42.673
I mean, it could be the same guy

01:42.741 --> 01:43.940
that went after Ben and Dilton,

01:44.009 --> 01:46.410
but they were
willing participants.

01:46.478 --> 01:48.011
Baby Teeth struggled.

01:48.080 --> 01:50.480
Maybe the brutality
of his death was the message.

01:50.549 --> 01:53.016
Like a warning that he's back

01:53.085 --> 01:54.217
and he's angry.

01:55.087 --> 01:56.153
The Gargoyle King?

01:56.221 --> 01:56.987
The real one.

02:04.563 --> 02:06.363
You already know
who I am, Betty.

02:06.432 --> 02:07.798
[BETTY] No.

02:07.866 --> 02:08.965
I don't have a clue.

02:09.033 --> 02:11.168
I've done a deep-dive
on the Internet,

02:11.236 --> 02:13.770
and there's no record of
anyone named Edgar Evernever.

02:18.911 --> 02:20.177
Many years ago,

02:21.146 --> 02:23.747
I was a very different man.

02:25.551 --> 02:30.787
My life was in tatters,
so I left it behind

02:30.856 --> 02:33.123
and I walked in the desert
to die.

02:33.192 --> 02:37.360
Till I stumbled upon a tree
on a hill beside a farm.

02:37.429 --> 02:39.496
I was in Death's clutches.

02:39.565 --> 02:43.233
And somehow I stumbled
to the door of that farm,

02:43.302 --> 02:45.102
and I knocked.

02:45.170 --> 02:46.036
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

02:47.306 --> 02:49.406
When I awoke,
I was in a white room.

02:49.475 --> 02:52.676
I was being tended to
by a kind, elderly farmer.

02:52.745 --> 02:54.611
And I said,
"How can I repay you?"

02:55.914 --> 02:57.981
So she put me to work
on her farm.

02:58.050 --> 03:01.251
I ploughed those fields,
and I sowed them with seed,

03:01.320 --> 03:05.055
and I watched them grow
into something beautiful.

03:06.158 --> 03:08.125
I felt reborn.

03:08.193 --> 03:11.094
After that,
I made it my sacred duty

03:11.163 --> 03:13.764
to open my own farm,

03:13.832 --> 03:17.901
where I could welcome lost
souls wandering in the darkness.

03:18.971 --> 03:20.203
It's a nice story,

03:20.272 --> 03:23.340
but it doesn't explain
how you've convinced my mom

03:23.408 --> 03:25.308
that she can see her dead son.

03:26.812 --> 03:29.079
Here we strive

03:29.148 --> 03:31.348
to create a safe place

03:31.416 --> 03:34.851
where wounded people can heal

03:34.920 --> 03:38.088
and become the best versions
of themselves.

03:38.724 --> 03:40.023
But, first,

03:40.092 --> 03:44.127
they must open themselves
to that process.

03:49.935 --> 03:53.570
No, but really, how does my mom
see her dead son?

03:53.639 --> 03:55.705
Do you have someone
dress up like Charles?

03:56.542 --> 03:58.842
[CHUCKLES]

04:03.482 --> 04:05.015
All right, boys, bring it in.

04:06.718 --> 04:08.518
Look, I know you're all pissed
about Baby Teeth...

04:08.587 --> 04:09.386
Damn right.

04:09.454 --> 04:11.288
And his killer will be caught.

04:11.356 --> 04:12.455
I swear to you.

04:12.524 --> 04:13.690
But, in the meantime,

04:14.827 --> 04:16.358
we honor our fallen brother.

04:16.428 --> 04:17.494
How the hell do we do that?

04:18.997 --> 04:21.031
I'm dedicating my next match
to Baby Teeth.

04:21.867 --> 04:24.134
No one asked you, Mad Dog.

04:24.203 --> 04:25.435
Why are you even here?

04:25.504 --> 04:27.137
Because Baby Teeth
was my brother, too.

04:27.206 --> 04:29.773
Wait, Mad Dog, what match?

04:29.842 --> 04:31.508
Did Elio already hook you up
with one?

04:31.577 --> 04:34.411
There's a boxing tournament this
weekend called the Gilded Gloves.

04:34.479 --> 04:36.346
I was gonna fight to win.

04:36.415 --> 04:38.882
But now, I'm gonna fight to
win and honor Baby Teeth.

04:42.287 --> 04:44.721
[VERONICA] <i> How's your boxing
career these days, Archie?</i>

04:44.790 --> 04:48.425
Your pal Elio is organizing a boxing
event called the Gilded Gloves.

04:48.493 --> 04:51.261
Brawny young men,
shirtless and in shorts, go on.

04:51.330 --> 04:55.632
I was thinking, maybe you could help get the
El Royale crew a spot in the tournament.

04:55.701 --> 04:57.834
The guys could use a win,
or at least a boost

04:57.903 --> 04:59.336
after what happened
to Baby Teeth.

05:00.138 --> 05:02.606
Let me see what I can do.

05:02.674 --> 05:06.009
Good morning, my dear Riverdale
High constituents and comrades.

05:06.078 --> 05:09.346
A lot of you have been asking about
the Farm's Student Advocacy group.

05:09.414 --> 05:11.248
Well, here'e the skinny.

05:13.352 --> 05:15.552
<i>Sign up sheets are posted
throughout the school.</i>

05:15.621 --> 05:17.420
<i>The club is open
to all students.</i>

05:17.489 --> 05:20.557
<i>Where the one become many,
and the many become one.</i>

05:21.393 --> 05:23.393
<i>So uncap those pens,</i>

05:23.462 --> 05:25.495
<i>sharpen those pencils,
and sign up.</i>

05:25.564 --> 05:27.998
<i>A little birdie told me it's
what all the cool kids are doing.</i>

05:30.969 --> 05:33.603
<i>Invasion of the Body Snatchers</i>
continues.

05:33.672 --> 05:35.205
So, let me get this straight,

05:35.274 --> 05:37.707
the reason Cheryl
is all-in on the Farm

05:37.776 --> 05:42.178
is that she gets to see
and talk to Jason?

05:42.247 --> 05:43.880
Yeah.

05:43.949 --> 05:47.183
My mom's entirely convinced that
she's seeing and talking to Charles,

05:47.252 --> 05:48.652
- her long-lost son.
- [VERONICA SCOFFS]

05:49.922 --> 05:52.422
What if you prove
that Charles was dead?

05:52.491 --> 05:54.157
I mean, your mom's lost touch
with reality,

05:54.226 --> 05:57.127
so maybe the best way to
snap her out of her delusions

05:57.195 --> 05:58.962
is with a harsh dose of truth.

05:59.031 --> 06:00.330
Like, prove
that Charles is dead.

06:00.399 --> 06:02.933
Or basically anything that
will refute these fantasies

06:03.001 --> 06:04.668
that Edgar Evernever
is spinning.

06:06.605 --> 06:11.207
No, unfortunately,
I only have a name, Charles Smith.

06:11.276 --> 06:13.243
He was raised
in the Sisters of Quiet Mercy,

06:13.312 --> 06:15.445
but they turned him out
when he was 18.

06:20.118 --> 06:21.718
Well, I appreciate you trying.

06:25.757 --> 06:27.023
[TONI] Betty.

06:27.092 --> 06:29.092
Whatever the Farm
did with Cheryl,

06:29.161 --> 06:30.894
I'm holding you responsible.

06:30.963 --> 06:33.063
How the hell did my girlfriend become
Queen of the Farmies overnight?

06:33.131 --> 06:34.331
It's Edgar.

06:35.000 --> 06:36.700
He is a con artist.

06:36.768 --> 06:40.170
He's somehow convinced
my mom and Cheryl

06:41.473 --> 06:44.841
[SIGHS] that they can,

06:44.910 --> 06:46.609
uh, talk to the dead.

06:47.913 --> 06:48.845
Excuse me?

06:51.116 --> 06:53.416
Cheryl thinks she's been
talking to Jason.

06:53.485 --> 06:54.751
She says she sees him.

06:54.820 --> 06:56.019
But Jason's dead.

06:57.189 --> 06:58.955
Everybody knows
that Jason's dead.

07:00.325 --> 07:02.092
True.

07:02.160 --> 07:04.928
And there's proof
that Jason's dead,

07:04.997 --> 07:06.896
that he was murdered.

07:06.965 --> 07:08.365
What are you talking about?

07:11.069 --> 07:12.168
Uh...

07:13.605 --> 07:18.541
I'm going to send you
a video, Toni,

07:20.779 --> 07:23.913
of Clifford Blossom
shooting Jason.

07:23.982 --> 07:26.216
I kept a copy of it
on my laptop.

07:26.918 --> 07:28.351
Show it to Cheryl,

07:28.420 --> 07:32.856
and hopefully it will be enough
to snap her back into reality.

07:34.226 --> 07:35.291
[CELL PHONE VIBRATES]

07:35.360 --> 07:36.326
Oh, hold on.
Will you give me a second?

07:36.395 --> 07:37.894
I think this is my dad.

07:39.197 --> 07:39.929
Hello.

07:43.869 --> 07:45.368
[STEAM HISSING]

07:50.342 --> 07:52.575
Veronica Lodge, don't suppose
I need to tell you

07:52.644 --> 07:54.377
this is a men's steam room.

07:54.446 --> 07:55.945
I came to talk business.

07:56.014 --> 07:57.047
[SIGHS]

07:58.717 --> 08:00.784
I want to get in
on the Gilded Gloves.

08:00.852 --> 08:02.419
You don't know the first thing
about boxing.

08:02.487 --> 08:05.388
Hmm. You'd be surprised
by what I know

08:05.457 --> 08:08.792
about hot, shirtless,
muscular bruisers.

08:10.128 --> 08:11.594
Starting with Archie Andrews.

08:11.663 --> 08:12.896
If memory serves,

08:12.964 --> 08:15.865
he almost beat your
prizefighter, Randy Ronson.

08:15.934 --> 08:16.966
[ELIO] Archie's a bum,

08:17.035 --> 08:18.835
and bums have no place
in my tournament.

08:18.904 --> 08:21.104
Now get the hell
out of my steam room.

08:23.175 --> 08:24.240
Fine.

08:26.378 --> 08:27.477
But remember this.

08:28.613 --> 08:31.081
Remember I tried
to keep things civil.

08:38.090 --> 08:40.623
[DR. CURDLE JR.] He suffered
a myriad of traumas,

08:40.692 --> 08:44.761
but our good friend here
died from loss of blood.

08:44.830 --> 08:46.629
From the pulling of his teeth,

08:46.698 --> 08:50.733
which occurred pre-mortem.

08:50.802 --> 08:54.604
There's one more ghoulish detail
I discovered during the autopsy.

08:56.174 --> 08:58.608
There was something lodged
in his throat.

09:00.545 --> 09:02.812
What the hell is that?

09:02.881 --> 09:05.381
A matchbook from the Maple Club.

09:05.450 --> 09:08.084
I thought
I'd seen the true face of evil.

09:08.753 --> 09:09.586
But this,

09:10.689 --> 09:14.924
whoever did this
isn't even human.

09:16.858 --> 09:20.163
