== <font color="#138CE9">https://</font>subscene<font color="#138CE9">.com</font> ==

09:21.325 --> 09:25.193
Any idea how one of your matchbooks
ended up in Baby Teeth's throat?

09:26.530 --> 09:29.931
Well, they are complimentary
to all of our guests.

09:30.000 --> 09:32.734
We don't recommend
they ingest them.

09:32.803 --> 09:37.272
I do recall this young man
being here a few nights ago.

09:37.341 --> 09:39.474
He was here with some friends.

09:39.543 --> 09:41.810
Ex-cons, but charming.

09:41.878 --> 09:44.913
Anyway, this Baby Teeth

09:44.982 --> 09:48.283
left the Maple Club
with a grin on his face,

09:48.352 --> 09:50.051
and alive.

09:50.120 --> 09:54.489
My girl Rosemary
fulfilled his fantasy.

09:54.558 --> 09:55.890
[WOMAN SCREAMING]

09:55.959 --> 09:57.392
What on Eve's Earth?

10:02.933 --> 10:04.633
[GROWLING]

10:06.000 --> 10:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

10:15.545 --> 10:17.045
All right, okay.

10:17.948 --> 10:20.548
Hey! [GRUNTS]

10:20.617 --> 10:23.318
I got him cuffed
in the back of my cruiser.

10:23.387 --> 10:24.753
He's not going anywhere.

10:24.821 --> 10:26.288
Is there anything else you guys
can tell us about him?

10:26.356 --> 10:28.256
Like his name
or where he's from?

10:31.595 --> 10:34.329
Martin, but they all
use an alias.

10:34.398 --> 10:35.997
Did something seem
different about him?

10:36.066 --> 10:37.599
Yes.

10:37.668 --> 10:41.336
Martin likes to take Fizzle
Rocks to enhance the experience,

10:41.405 --> 10:42.837
but this was different.

10:42.906 --> 10:44.306
The high hit him like a truck.

10:44.374 --> 10:46.007
He started foaming at the mouth,

10:46.076 --> 10:46.875
freaking out.

10:46.943 --> 10:48.176
This was helpful.

10:48.245 --> 10:50.612
If anything else comes up,
please give me a call.

10:54.785 --> 10:58.420
[ALICE] <i> And we are live in
three, two, one...</i>

10:58.488 --> 11:00.021
This is Alice Smith,

11:00.090 --> 11:01.923
and I am here with Veronica Lodge,

11:01.992 --> 11:04.859
promoter of the Southside's
El Royale Boxing Club.

11:04.928 --> 11:07.762
Veronica, would you like to tell us
about your latest business venture?

11:07.831 --> 11:09.297
Our athletic facility

11:09.366 --> 11:11.032
will help you reach
your fitness goals

11:11.101 --> 11:14.035
in a fun, classic,
competitive environment.

11:14.104 --> 11:17.605
Our trained staff features some of
the toughest fighters in the state,

11:17.674 --> 11:21.309
including up-and-coming boxer
Archie Andrews.

11:21.378 --> 11:22.310
Archie?

11:23.613 --> 11:25.180
Hi, I'm Archie Andrews,

11:25.248 --> 11:27.882
owner, trainer, and fighter here
at the El Royale Boxing Club.

11:27.951 --> 11:29.317
Join now, and your first three

11:29.386 --> 11:32.654
personal training sessions
with me are completely free.

11:34.925 --> 11:38.059
I got one more thing to say,
a message for Randy Ronson.

11:38.128 --> 11:39.961
This Friday night
at the Gilded Gloves,

11:40.030 --> 11:41.663
I want my rematch.

11:41.732 --> 11:43.231
Me and you.

11:43.300 --> 11:44.599
Let's settle this for good.

11:46.403 --> 11:48.870
Strong words from a local hero.

11:48.939 --> 11:52.774
Live from the Southside,
I'm Alice Smith, RIVW.

11:54.678 --> 11:57.011
[HAL] <i> Your mother has
thrown down the gauntlet.</i>

11:57.748 --> 11:59.748
She's filed for divorce.

11:59.816 --> 12:01.750
Her lawyers issued
the papers today,

12:01.818 --> 12:03.785
but I haven't signed yet.

12:03.854 --> 12:06.388
Has she started seeing someone?

12:06.456 --> 12:08.790
Well, she does spend most
of her time at the Farm,

12:08.859 --> 12:10.492
presumably with Edgar.

12:10.560 --> 12:12.127
Who's a con artist.

12:12.195 --> 12:14.596
He's got her thinking
she's seeing Charles.

12:14.664 --> 12:16.431
That's impossible,
Charles is dead.

12:16.500 --> 12:18.433
Yeah, but I don't have
physical proof of that.

12:18.502 --> 12:20.368
I don't have a body,
I don't have ashes.

12:22.806 --> 12:26.007
You know, you don't need
a body or ashes, Betty,

12:26.910 --> 12:28.042
just a stone.

12:30.080 --> 12:31.413
A piece of granite will do.

12:34.084 --> 12:36.718
[ELIO] <i> I must admit, that was a bold
move, challenging Randy.</i>

12:36.787 --> 12:38.953
So does that mean
the El Royale boxers

12:39.022 --> 12:41.055
will get to be part
of the Gilded Gloves?

12:41.124 --> 12:42.690
Yes.

12:42.759 --> 12:44.592
Only thing is, your boy's going
to have to move up a weight class.

12:44.661 --> 12:46.728
Randy's fighting in
the middleweight division now.

12:46.797 --> 12:48.229
[SIGHS]

12:49.065 --> 12:50.498
- Fine.
- Great.

12:51.201 --> 12:52.233
I'm hosting at my gym.

12:52.302 --> 12:53.935
[CHUCKLES] Nice try.

12:54.004 --> 12:55.537
We'll flip for the venue.

12:57.908 --> 13:00.141
Heads for Archie's gym,
tails for your gym.

13:06.716 --> 13:07.916
Heads.

13:07.984 --> 13:10.251
We'll see you at the El Royale.

13:12.656 --> 13:14.122
When he finally comes down,
we'll ask him

13:14.191 --> 13:15.857
where he got the Fizzle Rocks.

13:15.926 --> 13:17.559
- My bet is still Kurtz.
- [SIGHS]

13:17.627 --> 13:20.462
Wouldn't mind asking him if he knows
anything about Baby Teeth, either.

13:20.530 --> 13:23.731
I'll have Forensics run a test on
the Fizzle Rocks he had on him.

13:28.638 --> 13:30.305
[CHERYL] <i> Why would you show this to me?</i>

13:30.373 --> 13:33.541
[TONI] Because you needed
to be reminded of the truth.

13:33.610 --> 13:36.478
Cheryl, you're not talking
to Jason at the Farm.

13:36.546 --> 13:39.914
The truth is all right there,
in this video.

13:39.983 --> 13:43.585
Toni, this video
is clearly fabricated.

13:43.653 --> 13:46.654
With technology these days,
anything is possible.

13:46.723 --> 13:49.390
Detractors can spin
any story they want.

13:51.862 --> 13:53.294
Cheryl, have

13:54.598 --> 13:57.765
you ever hugged Jason?

14:00.303 --> 14:02.937
Yes. Of course.

14:03.006 --> 14:04.639
Now enough of this third degree.

14:12.449 --> 14:13.615
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

14:14.451 --> 14:15.183
Betty?

14:17.153 --> 14:18.019
Mom,

14:19.422 --> 14:21.489
are you engaged to Edgar?

14:21.558 --> 14:22.357
[SIGHS]

14:23.927 --> 14:27.328
Edgar and I have a deep
understanding of one another.

14:29.132 --> 14:30.198
That's what I thought.

14:32.602 --> 14:33.968
I want to show you something.

14:39.676 --> 14:41.142
[ALICE] What is this, Betty?

14:44.314 --> 14:48.483
I paid someone to help me
track down Charles' grave.

14:48.552 --> 14:49.751
I'm so sorry, Mom,

14:49.819 --> 14:52.587
but you haven't been
talking to him at the Farm.

14:53.156 --> 14:54.289
Your son

14:55.425 --> 14:58.660
has been here, dead and buried,

14:58.728 --> 15:00.328
for the last five years.

15:08.705 --> 15:09.904
[SIGHS HEAVILY]

15:09.973 --> 15:11.539
It's just so sad.

15:13.977 --> 15:14.876
I know, Mom.

15:16.780 --> 15:20.248
So sad that you won't let me
be happy at the Farm.

15:22.752 --> 15:25.019
I don't know when
you're gonna give up, Betty.

15:27.591 --> 15:28.590
[SIGHS]

15:29.826 --> 15:31.793
You saw his gravestone.

15:31.861 --> 15:33.161
I'm sorry, Betty,

15:34.431 --> 15:36.431
but I spoke to my son
this morning.

15:41.838 --> 15:43.938
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

15:49.446 --> 15:50.545
I'm sorry, too, Mom.

15:51.915 --> 15:53.414
[ALICE GASPING]

15:56.319 --> 15:58.252
[SLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

16:02.859 --> 16:04.092
Bon appetit, champ.

16:05.195 --> 16:07.862
You're making up
for lost calories.

16:07.931 --> 16:09.130
Ronnie, I feel like Jughead.

16:09.199 --> 16:10.999
That's the idea, Archie.

16:13.937 --> 16:15.737
[REFEREE] <i> Randy Ronson to the scale.</i>

16:15.805 --> 16:17.271
[CAMERAS CLICKING]

16:19.442 --> 16:21.609
- 159 pounds.
- [PEOPLE APPLAUDING]

16:22.112 --> 16:23.378
[GRUNTS]

16:27.651 --> 16:29.283
Archie Andrews to the scale.

16:41.264 --> 16:44.265
154 pounds.

16:44.334 --> 16:45.633
[PEOPLE APPLAUDING]

17:04.721 --> 17:06.186
Where am I?

17:06.256 --> 17:07.789
What did you do to me?

17:07.857 --> 17:09.357
I chloroformed you.

17:10.260 --> 17:12.426
Don't worry, Mom, you're safe.

17:18.243 --> 17:22.579
Edgar always starts with questions,
so I'll do the same.

17:23.482 --> 17:25.515
Do you remember this?

17:25.584 --> 17:27.550
It was your first day at
<i>The Riverdale Register.</i>

17:27.619 --> 17:29.019
You were so excited.

17:29.088 --> 17:32.322
And now I'm an on-air reporter
for RIVW, thanks to the Farm.

17:34.960 --> 17:36.726
Eighth grade graduation.

17:38.930 --> 17:40.964
You cried that day,
do you remember?

17:41.032 --> 17:42.232
That's the past.

17:44.069 --> 17:45.368
I'm someone else now.

17:45.437 --> 17:46.736
No, no.

17:46.805 --> 17:47.937
The past is

17:48.940 --> 17:50.907
part of who you are.

17:50.976 --> 17:52.442
You're Alice Cooper.

17:52.511 --> 17:54.411
You bought a house
on Elm Street.

17:54.479 --> 17:55.979
You painted our front door red...

17:56.047 --> 17:57.847
[TEARFULLY] I lived with
a murderer in that house.

17:57.916 --> 18:00.617
[TEARFULLY] You raised
me and Polly in it, too.

18:00.685 --> 18:03.153
Bad things happen, but you
can't get rid of your past

18:03.221 --> 18:05.688
because then you'd
lose the good parts, too.

18:07.959 --> 18:10.093
There's been so much pain.

18:10.162 --> 18:12.962
I know. I know.

18:13.031 --> 18:15.165
But that's what
makes us stronger.

18:15.233 --> 18:17.901
Edgar doesn't see that.
You have to believe me.

18:19.571 --> 18:20.570
Believe you?

18:22.107 --> 18:23.373
Okay.

18:23.442 --> 18:25.241
So tell me the truth, Betty.

18:26.545 --> 18:28.278
Was that really Charles' grave?

18:34.486 --> 18:36.085
So how can I trust you?

18:36.154 --> 18:37.520
You lied to me!

18:37.589 --> 18:40.623
You faked a gravestone.

18:40.692 --> 18:43.593
Look, I love you,
I love you, Betty.

18:45.730 --> 18:47.964
But you're gonna
have to let me go.

18:52.671 --> 18:53.903
I'm sorry, Mom.

18:55.240 --> 18:56.139
No.

18:56.208 --> 18:57.440
I have to go to school,

18:57.509 --> 18:59.943
but I'll come back
to check on you.

19:00.011 --> 19:01.077
No, no, Betty.

19:03.849 --> 19:05.281
This is your life.

19:05.350 --> 19:06.416
Look at it

19:07.452 --> 19:09.419
and remember who you are.

19:14.125 --> 19:14.958
[SOFTLY] Betty.

19:20.398 --> 19:22.165
[SNIFFLES]

19:22.234 --> 19:24.434
[JUGHEAD] <i> You locked your
mom in Dilton's bunker?</i>

19:27.239 --> 19:29.806
Yeah, it's the only place
where she'll be safe

19:29.875 --> 19:31.407
from the Farm, Jug.

19:31.476 --> 19:33.610
And I've already made some
headway with the deprogramming.

19:33.678 --> 19:35.512
Next, I'm gonna listen
to her testimony tapes,

19:35.580 --> 19:38.448
and see if there's anything I can
use to help me get my mom back.

19:38.517 --> 19:39.315
[BANGING]

19:40.852 --> 19:42.151
What is that?

19:49.261 --> 19:50.793
What the hell is going on?

19:52.097 --> 19:54.264
Hey, did she take something?

19:54.332 --> 19:55.865
Yeah, she took some "G."

19:56.801 --> 19:58.167
Get her to the infirmary.

20:02.374 --> 20:03.940
[CELL PHONE VIBRATES]

20:04.009 --> 20:05.508
Hey, Dad.

20:05.577 --> 20:07.377
Jug, I need your brain, boy.

20:07.445 --> 20:09.479
I got another guy here
on a nasty trip.

20:09.548 --> 20:11.381
<i>Can you meet me at the station?</i>

20:13.552 --> 20:14.884
Yeah, I'll be right there.

20:16.588 --> 20:17.353
Okay.

20:20.759 --> 20:22.125
It's gotta be a bad batch.

20:22.193 --> 20:23.293
[PRISONER MUTTERING AND BANGING]

20:23.361 --> 20:25.428
One that causes
Fizzle Rock psychosis.

20:29.167 --> 20:31.501
Or the Fizzle Rocks are
being cut with something.

20:31.570 --> 20:32.769
Bath salts, maybe.

20:32.837 --> 20:34.971
We need to catch whoever's
dealing this garbage

20:35.040 --> 20:36.406
before someone turns up dead.

20:39.411 --> 20:41.377
Looks like our john
is almost ready to talk.

20:41.446 --> 20:43.079
[PRISONER PANTING]

20:54.993 --> 20:56.125
[TONI GASPS]

20:57.295 --> 20:58.261
Evelyn.

20:59.531 --> 21:00.530
What are you doing?

21:01.333 --> 21:02.999
Toni,

21:03.068 --> 21:06.269
you're detracting Cheryl
from her studies at the Farm,

21:07.205 --> 21:08.738
but I'm not gonna
let you ruin her.

21:08.807 --> 21:12.208
"Ruin her"?
Bitch, I love her.

21:12.277 --> 21:13.643
And she loves me.

21:17.315 --> 21:18.848
The Farm

21:18.917 --> 21:22.518
is fulfilling Cheryl in ways
you can't even begin to imagine.

21:27.359 --> 21:29.392
I find that hard to believe.

21:33.732 --> 21:35.298
Have a blessed day.

21:43.508 --> 21:44.307
Andrews.

21:45.510 --> 21:47.543
Mad Dog, what're you doing here?

21:47.612 --> 21:49.412
There's something you
need to know about Randy.

21:50.649 --> 21:52.081
He's juicing.

21:52.150 --> 21:53.583
What, he's taking steroids?

21:53.652 --> 21:55.585
No, something new.

21:55.654 --> 21:57.620
A powder.
I saw Elio give it to him.

21:58.323 --> 22:00.023
Made him crazy strong.

22:00.091 --> 22:01.224
Elio's scared.

22:01.926 --> 22:02.925
He thinks I might win.

22:02.994 --> 22:05.128
No, man,
you're not listening to me.

22:05.196 --> 22:06.929
I looked into Randy's eyes,

22:06.998 --> 22:08.931
and it wasn't Randy anymore.

22:09.000 --> 22:10.099
It was rage.

22:10.168 --> 22:11.968
He'll kill you.

22:12.037 --> 22:14.804
Unless you take something
to level the playing field.

22:16.541 --> 22:18.641
- Here.
- No, dude.

22:19.711 --> 22:20.910
I don't take that stuff.

22:20.979 --> 22:22.612
When you see Randy in the ring,

22:23.281 --> 22:24.514
you might want to.

22:25.684 --> 22:26.883
Just in case.

22:35.894 --> 22:37.026
Thirteen.

22:37.095 --> 22:37.894
What does that mean?

22:39.564 --> 22:41.597
It's a good roll.

22:41.666 --> 22:43.866
Sadly, your Elven army
is no match

22:43.935 --> 22:45.835
for the legions of Gargoyles
at your doorstep.

22:48.506 --> 22:50.006
It's okay, JB.

22:50.075 --> 22:52.508
You got further in this quest
than I did at your level.

22:54.079 --> 22:55.945
Could we play another round?

22:56.014 --> 22:59.449
You sure your parents won't
mind you staying out so long?

22:59.517 --> 23:01.851
Nah, it's like I told you
when we met,

23:01.920 --> 23:02.985
they're busy.

23:04.022 --> 23:05.354
Same with my parents.

23:08.593 --> 23:09.525
[ROLLS DICE]

23:11.563 --> 23:12.829
[JUGHEAD] What does it mean?

23:16.000 --> 23:18.067
The "G's" for "Gargoyle,"
I think.

23:18.136 --> 23:19.769
Which Gargoyle?

23:19.838 --> 23:21.137
Is there anyone in particular?

23:21.206 --> 23:22.739
This time it was a guy
named Kurtz.

23:26.578 --> 23:28.244
Do you have any idea
where Kurtz is now?

23:28.313 --> 23:29.345
How should I know?

23:33.251 --> 23:36.719
Kurtz is the cook,
and he's selling, too.

23:36.788 --> 23:38.187
But we need the kingpin.

23:38.256 --> 23:40.289
I'm gonna pay Hiram Lodge
a visit.

23:40.358 --> 23:41.858
Tell your mom I'll be home late.

23:52.036 --> 23:53.035
Mom?

23:54.272 --> 23:56.205
Mom, are you okay?

23:56.274 --> 23:57.039
What...

24:15.410 --> 24:16.176
Betty.

24:18.547 --> 24:20.046
[SIGHS] Evelyn.

24:20.115 --> 24:23.116
You wouldn't happen to know
where your mom is, would you?

24:23.185 --> 24:25.485
Am I my mother's keeper?

24:25.554 --> 24:27.520
Well, she missed
bed check last night.

24:27.589 --> 24:30.623
But someone did see you
visiting her room yesterday.

24:30.692 --> 24:33.193
Hmm, well, I'll let you know
if I see her.

24:34.730 --> 24:38.164
We have copies
of those tapes, Betty.

24:38.233 --> 24:40.200
And copies of those copies.

24:47.709 --> 24:50.343
Let me make
something very clear.

24:50.412 --> 24:54.147
You and your dad
may have brainwashed my mom,

24:54.216 --> 24:57.617
but I see right through your
enlightened Farmie crap.

24:57.686 --> 24:59.652
So stop messing with me,

24:59.721 --> 25:01.521
stop messing with my family,

25:01.590 --> 25:03.590
and stop messing
with my friends.

25:03.658 --> 25:08.695
Better yet, don't even think about
coming near me or my mom ever again.

25:10.232 --> 25:12.766
Because if you do, Evelyn,

25:13.502 --> 25:15.368
I will kill you.

25:15.437 --> 25:17.570
And if you don't believe me,
ask around.

25:17.639 --> 25:19.739
People will tell you
what I'm capable of.

25:29.918 --> 25:32.852
Cheryl, are you going
to a meeting at the Farm?

25:32.921 --> 25:35.989
Indeed, my love.

25:36.058 --> 25:39.059
Do you think these Louboutins are
too flashy for kombucha brewing?

25:41.463 --> 25:43.096
Well...

25:43.165 --> 25:44.464
How about if you didn't go?

25:45.400 --> 25:46.966
Why wouldn't I?

25:47.035 --> 25:48.268
The Farm needs me tonight.

25:48.336 --> 25:50.003
I need you tonight.

25:50.072 --> 25:53.039
I need you in every way.

25:53.108 --> 25:54.107
Mind,

25:55.277 --> 25:56.476
body,

25:57.312 --> 25:58.545
soul.

25:58.613 --> 26:01.815
But, uh, mostly body.

26:17.499 --> 26:18.698
[ARCHIE] <i> Tomorrow,</i>
<i>when we fight,</i>

26:19.634 --> 26:20.633
we fight for him.

26:21.436 --> 26:22.836
For Baby Teeth.

26:49.397 --> 26:51.764
[FP] <i> He's the guy</i>
<i>I collared at Pop's.</i>

26:51.833 --> 26:53.800
Finally woke up,
that's when I called you.

26:54.703 --> 26:56.002
Hey.

26:57.639 --> 26:59.405
You could've really
hurt someone, pal.

26:59.474 --> 27:01.875
Where'd you get the G?
From a guy named Kurtz?

27:01.943 --> 27:02.709
[MAN] Yeah.

27:04.045 --> 27:05.245
He wasn't my usual dealer.

27:05.313 --> 27:06.946
- [CELL PHONE VIBRATING]
- He was real aggressive.

27:07.015 --> 27:08.882
Trying to get me to buy
more than my usual.

27:08.950 --> 27:10.750
He's still in Riverdale.

27:10.819 --> 27:12.252
He's getting desperate,
it sounds like.

27:12.320 --> 27:13.920
Hmm. It's Laura.

27:13.989 --> 27:16.189
Our lady friend
from the Maple Club.

27:17.125 --> 27:18.057
Hello.

27:19.394 --> 27:21.828
[ALICE ON TAPE] <i> She's just so
angry, Edgar.</i>

27:23.765 --> 27:25.832
[EDGAR] <i> Alice, Betty loves you.</i>

27:26.835 --> 27:27.867
<i>She's a good person.</i>

27:31.006 --> 27:33.072
[ALICE] <i> It's just the two
of us in the house now,</i>

27:33.141 --> 27:34.207
<i>and the truth is,</i>

27:35.076 --> 27:36.743
<i>I'm afraid of Betty.</i>

27:36.811 --> 27:38.411
<i>Sometimes, the way
she looks at me,</i>

27:38.480 --> 27:39.279
<i>I think she's</i>

27:40.182 --> 27:41.648
<i>going to hurt me.</i>

27:41.716 --> 27:43.783
<i>I think she wants to hurt me.</i>

27:43.852 --> 27:45.251
<i>She's her father's daughter.</i>

27:45.320 --> 27:48.121
<i>She has the same darkness
in her that I saw in him.</i>

27:59.192 --> 28:00.258
What happened?

28:00.327 --> 28:01.926
Another crazy john?

28:01.995 --> 28:04.496
You told me to call
in case anything came up.

28:04.564 --> 28:06.464
Well, some preppy rich kids
were here,

28:06.533 --> 28:08.266
rowdy and stirring up trouble.

28:08.335 --> 28:10.669
Were they on the same Rocks that
drove the other customer feral?

28:10.737 --> 28:12.871
No, but they were
here killing time

28:12.939 --> 28:14.339
before meeting a dealer
in the lobby.

28:14.408 --> 28:15.707
But I guess the guy
never showed.

28:15.776 --> 28:16.908
How'd you get rid of them?

28:16.977 --> 28:18.710
[PENELOPE] One of the ruffians got a call.

28:18.779 --> 28:21.346
Sounded like a supplier
looking to reschedule.

28:21.415 --> 28:23.381
He said something about a fight.

28:23.450 --> 28:24.949
Left this in the trash.

28:28.355 --> 28:29.754
That's Archie's gym.

28:29.823 --> 28:31.990
One last chance to bust Kurtz.

28:33.326 --> 28:34.793
What did you do to my mom?

28:34.861 --> 28:36.528
What did you do to make her say

28:36.596 --> 28:39.097
such horrible things about me
on those tapes?

28:39.166 --> 28:41.633
Why are you trying to turn her
against me?

28:43.570 --> 28:45.203
Betty,

28:45.272 --> 28:47.572
everything your mother
said on those tapes,

28:49.142 --> 28:50.875
those were her own words.

28:50.944 --> 28:52.577
And, to be fair,

28:52.646 --> 28:55.814
you have given Alice some
legitimate reasons to fear you.

28:55.882 --> 28:59.317
You're not turning this
around on me.

28:59.386 --> 29:02.220
Not while you keep
feeding her lies,

29:02.289 --> 29:03.488
telling her that Charles...

29:03.557 --> 29:05.657
Charles is a wound.

29:05.726 --> 29:06.958
She needs to heal.

29:07.027 --> 29:08.326
Charles is dead.

29:09.096 --> 29:09.828
He's a ghost.

29:09.896 --> 29:12.197
Your mother is on a journey,

29:12.265 --> 29:13.932
and she's making
tremendous progress

29:14.000 --> 29:16.501
towards finding her truest self.

29:16.570 --> 29:18.403
She could've done that at home,

29:18.472 --> 29:19.504
with a therapist.

29:19.573 --> 29:21.706
She didn't have
to give away my money,

29:21.775 --> 29:23.842
our house, everything!

29:24.878 --> 29:28.012
Ah, you know, I think, Betty,

29:30.150 --> 29:32.851
you and your mother see the
world quite differently.

29:33.587 --> 29:34.886
You don't need us.

29:35.489 --> 29:36.588
She does.

29:36.656 --> 29:38.389
She needs to heal from the pain

29:38.458 --> 29:40.692
that has been
inflicted upon her.

29:40.761 --> 29:44.662
Communing with Charles,
real or illusionary,

29:45.899 --> 29:47.132
comforts her.

29:47.200 --> 29:51.870
Fills her in a way that no one
in her life can or does.

29:52.873 --> 29:54.672
Including you.

29:54.741 --> 29:57.175
Now, I ask you, why,

29:58.545 --> 30:00.845
in your mind,
is that a bad thing?

30:04.351 --> 30:06.551
[METAL CLANKING]

30:21.168 --> 30:22.567
We're going somewhere.

30:23.303 --> 30:24.435
[CAR DOOR CLOSING]

30:42.622 --> 30:43.721
It's okay, Mom.

30:45.458 --> 30:49.260
Evelyn will make sure
you get home safely.

31:03.710 --> 31:05.443
Take care of her, Evelyn.

31:06.546 --> 31:07.879
[VOICE BREAKS] Please.

31:12.619 --> 31:14.586
That's all we've
ever wanted to do.

31:26.199 --> 31:27.332
[ARCHIE] <i> What is this for?</i>

31:27.400 --> 31:28.466
It's for luck.

31:36.676 --> 31:38.276
- [ARCHIE GASPS]
- [CHUCKLES]

31:41.047 --> 31:42.614
I'm pretty sure
they're your size.

31:42.682 --> 31:43.882
Thank you, Ronnie.

31:43.950 --> 31:45.316
Thank you for believing in me.

31:47.854 --> 31:49.287
No matter what happens,

31:50.857 --> 31:52.790
I want you to know that

31:52.859 --> 31:54.292
I'm always in your corner.

32:03.603 --> 32:05.270
I should go.
Still lots to do.

32:05.338 --> 32:06.237
Yeah.

32:06.306 --> 32:07.272
Yeah.

32:07.941 --> 32:09.007
- Okay.
- Okay.

32:09.075 --> 32:10.208
- Bye.
- See you later.

32:14.814 --> 32:15.647
[DOOR CLOSES]

32:17.117 --> 32:19.984
Flying a little close
to the sun there, aren't you?

32:21.254 --> 32:22.987
We're friends now, Dad.

32:23.056 --> 32:24.489
Uh-huh. Yeah.

32:25.225 --> 32:26.024
Friends.

32:32.866 --> 32:34.365
[SCHOOL BELL RINGING]

32:42.008 --> 32:43.308
[CHERYL SNIFFLES]

32:44.844 --> 32:45.910
T.T.

32:47.380 --> 32:48.346
Are you okay?

32:49.916 --> 32:52.016
[SIGHS] Evelyn said

32:52.786 --> 32:54.218
I have to make a choice.

32:56.289 --> 32:57.388
Jason

32:58.358 --> 32:59.190
or you.

33:00.527 --> 33:03.728
Cheryl, Jason's a ghost.

33:04.898 --> 33:06.364
I'm right here.

33:08.068 --> 33:09.734
You love me.

33:12.539 --> 33:14.138
[TEARFULLY] I'm sorry, Toni.

33:14.708 --> 33:16.040
I do love you.

33:19.045 --> 33:20.845
But I've loved Jason
my whole life.

33:22.148 --> 33:23.581
Cheryl.

33:23.650 --> 33:25.516
I'm not gonna let this happen.

33:25.585 --> 33:28.286
There has to be a way
you can be with me

33:30.190 --> 33:31.389
and Jason.

33:32.225 --> 33:33.925
[CHERYL SNIFFLES]

33:35.028 --> 33:35.927
There is.

33:37.497 --> 33:39.230
If you're willing
to open your mind to it.

34:01.955 --> 34:05.556
[ALICE ON TAPE] <i> Betty won't admit it,
but I know she was deeply hurt by Hal.</i>

34:05.625 --> 34:06.791
<i>We all were.</i>

34:06.860 --> 34:08.226
<i>But she took it the hardest.</i>

34:09.496 --> 34:10.328
[TURNS OFF TAPE]

34:12.032 --> 34:12.929
How'd it go?

34:12.998 --> 34:14.197
Great.

34:14.266 --> 34:15.900
No one suspects anything.

34:21.875 --> 34:22.840
Toni,

34:27.213 --> 34:28.713
I'm not a monster,

34:30.817 --> 34:32.050
- am I?
- No.

34:34.920 --> 34:37.621
You're a daughter
who wants her mother back.

34:39.259 --> 34:41.426
Just like I want
my girlfriend back.

34:52.138 --> 34:55.172
[POLICE RADIO CHATTER]

34:58.745 --> 35:00.378
- There he is. Kurtz.
- Where?

35:00.447 --> 35:02.513
In the hoodie.
He's walking towards the alley.

35:13.326 --> 35:15.126
[SIREN BLARING]

35:18.364 --> 35:19.330
[FP] Hold it!

35:19.399 --> 35:20.631
Put your hands up.

35:20.700 --> 35:22.366
Don't you move.

35:22.435 --> 35:23.734
Get 'em up!

35:25.939 --> 35:27.438
[POLICE RADIO CHATTER]

35:30.844 --> 35:32.710
You and your drugs are done
for good, Kurtz.

35:42.355 --> 35:44.355
[CROWD CHEERING]

35:54.300 --> 35:55.366
[JOSIE] You nervous?

35:56.369 --> 35:57.401
Not a bit.

35:58.671 --> 36:01.405
- Is that a new robe?
- And trunks.

36:01.474 --> 36:03.708
Pop's Chock'lit Shoppe
is Archie's official sponsor.

36:03.776 --> 36:04.742
You like 'em?

36:09.949 --> 36:11.949
I'm gonna end Andrews tonight.
I got this.

36:12.018 --> 36:14.719
You said that last time,
and he almost beat you.

36:17.590 --> 36:18.623
What the hell's in that?

36:18.691 --> 36:20.024
Little last-minute boost.

36:20.093 --> 36:22.026
I dissolved some G
into your water.

36:25.031 --> 36:27.999
Now get in there
and live up to your promise.

36:36.342 --> 36:38.209
[CROWD CHEERING]

36:44.717 --> 36:46.217
[OPERATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

36:52.992 --> 36:54.358
I'll admit, Betty, I'm surprised

36:54.427 --> 36:56.594
you've asked me to sign
these divorce papers.

36:58.431 --> 37:00.097
Well, that makes two of us.

37:05.705 --> 37:07.538
Why the change of heart?

37:10.643 --> 37:14.579
[SIGHS] I finally realized
that it's time to let Mom go.

37:16.349 --> 37:19.884
She needs to heal
in whatever way she chooses.

37:22.855 --> 37:23.788
[CLEARS THROAT]

37:25.992 --> 37:29.760
I wonder, Betty, if you would
consider doing me a favor as well.

37:31.864 --> 37:33.431
What kind of favor?

37:34.334 --> 37:35.967
Oh, it's nothing much.

37:40.039 --> 37:41.439
I just want to come home.

37:43.943 --> 37:45.443
[CROWD SHOUTING]

37:48.748 --> 37:49.947
Attaboy, Arch, stick and move.

38:09.469 --> 38:11.469
Come on, kid,
get the hell out of there!

38:12.505 --> 38:14.405
[CROWD CHEERING]

38:14.474 --> 38:15.673
[BELL DINGS]

38:15.742 --> 38:18.042
[BELL DINGING]

38:22.649 --> 38:24.315
You got to stay
off the ropes, kid.

38:26.919 --> 38:28.452
Something's wrong.

38:28.521 --> 38:30.588
Ronson's on
some kind of crazy drug.

38:30.657 --> 38:32.156
The ref needs to call the fight.

38:35.628 --> 38:36.961
Hey, Ref.

38:37.030 --> 38:39.330
Ronson looks like he wants
to chew off my fighter's face.

38:39.399 --> 38:40.698
We want a disqualification.

38:40.767 --> 38:42.867
Only way this match ends
is if you forfeit, Andrews.

38:42.935 --> 38:44.168
You wanna take the loss?

38:45.438 --> 38:47.571
Screw you, Elio.

38:47.640 --> 38:49.807
Look, he's going to have
himself a hell of a hangover,

38:49.876 --> 38:52.510
but I need you to knock him out
in this round.

38:52.578 --> 38:54.578
I don't know. I don't know.

38:54.647 --> 38:56.647
The overhand right
is there for you.

38:56.716 --> 38:58.282
Okay? Once you see a crack
in his armor,

38:58.351 --> 39:00.651
you bring out the hacksaw,
you understand?

39:00.720 --> 39:01.952
- [BELL DINGS]
- [REFEREE] Seconds out!

39:02.588 --> 39:03.721
Let's do it.

39:03.790 --> 39:05.690
[CROWD CHEERING]

39:12.632 --> 39:13.731
[BELL DINGS]

39:38.791 --> 39:40.124
[BOTH WHOOPING]

39:40.193 --> 39:41.158
Attaboy!

39:41.227 --> 39:43.828
[REFEREE] ...two, three, four...

39:43.896 --> 39:47.965
- five, six, seven, eight,
- [CROWD CHANTING] Archie!

39:48.034 --> 39:49.900
...nine, ten.

39:49.969 --> 39:51.202
- It's over.
- [BELL DINGS]

39:51.270 --> 39:53.904
[CROWD CONTINUES CHEERING]

40:01.647 --> 40:02.646
Ronson?

40:03.383 --> 40:04.815
We need a doctor.

40:04.884 --> 40:06.283
Somebody call a doctor!

40:07.353 --> 40:08.586
Ronson, wake up.

40:09.756 --> 40:11.322
[FP] You've hurt
a lot of people, Kurtz.

40:11.391 --> 40:12.656
What were you thinking?

40:12.725 --> 40:14.892
Sell the bad batch,
get out of town,

40:14.961 --> 40:16.327
dodge a murder charge?

40:22.769 --> 40:23.868
Why Baby Teeth?

40:23.936 --> 40:25.970
Did the Gargoyle King
demand a sacrifice?

40:27.440 --> 40:28.606
Baby Teeth.

40:30.276 --> 40:32.109
[CHUCKLING] He was only
the warm-up.

40:34.147 --> 40:35.246
To what?

40:35.314 --> 40:36.947
To the ultimate quest.

40:37.917 --> 40:40.050
To one final game

40:40.753 --> 40:41.752
for you

40:42.889 --> 40:44.288
and your family,

40:45.091 --> 40:46.323
Hellcaster.

40:47.160 --> 40:49.260
It was demanded by the King.

40:51.063 --> 40:53.330
Save the Little Princess.

40:57.970 --> 40:59.870
- Jellybean?
- What the hell did you do?

40:59.939 --> 41:01.172
[SHOUTS] What did you do?

41:02.208 --> 41:04.041
She's been summoned

41:04.110 --> 41:05.743
by the King.

41:05.812 --> 41:09.013
[LAUGHING MANIACALLY]

41:13.386 --> 41:14.718
I don't understand.

41:14.787 --> 41:16.620
Why couldn't we just
keep playing in Pop's?

41:16.689 --> 41:18.189
Because, Princess Jellybean,

41:19.025 --> 41:20.191
he wanted to meet you.

41:20.726 --> 41:21.692
Who did?

41:23.596 --> 41:25.362
[CRACKLING]

41:25.431 --> 41:27.331
[LOW GROWL]

